<Link id="l00279" /><CodeLine lineNumber="279"><span class="doxyHighlight">    </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// &#42; Ignore option candidates with empty names, such as &quot;--&quot;, or names</span></CodeLine>

<Link id="l00288" /><CodeLine lineNumber="288"><span class="doxyHighlight">    </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// &#42; Ignore positional argument option candidates (which do not</span></CodeLine>

<Link id="l00293" /><CodeLine lineNumber="293"><span class="doxyHighlight">    </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// Now check if the candidate ends with a character commonly used when</span></CodeLine>

<Link id="l00306" /><CodeLine lineNumber="306"><span class="doxyHighlight">    </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// Consider each possible prefix for each candidate to find the most</span></CodeLine>

<Link id="l00312" /><CodeLine lineNumber="312"><span class="doxyHighlight">      </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// If Candidate and NormalizedName have more than &#39;BestDistance&#39;</span></CodeLine>
